PAUSE
================================================================================
LUDUZO autonomous build — HARD MODE (ThinkerThinker A23)

PAUSED 2026-07-07 by founder command <Pause>. Working tree clean and pushed.
To RESUME, change this first line back to  ACTIVE .

The FIRST LINE of this file is the control switch, read by the Stop hook
(.claude/hooks/build-continue-guard.mjs). Only the first non-empty line matters;
everything below is notes. Wrapping <> and quotes are ignored, so <ACTIVE>,
<Pause>, "STOP" all work.

  • ACTIVE  → the agent may NOT stop. Every attempt to end a turn is blocked and
             the agent keeps building. There is no self-authorized stop.

  • PAUSE   → the founder's <Pause> command. The agent is allowed to stop and hold.
  • STOP    → the founder's <Stop> command. The agent is allowed to stop.
             (HALT / STAND DOWN / END / DONE / CEASE also work.)

HOW THE FOUNDER HALTS IT:
  • Type <Pause> or <Stop> in chat  → the agent writes that word to this first line
        and stops, OR
  • Edit this first line yourself to  PAUSE  or  STOP , OR
  • Delete this file.

Nothing else — not "hard-blocked", not "nothing buildable", not "waiting on you" —
lets the agent stop. Only your <Pause>/<Stop> command.
